What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Curing Agents Market?

Market Analysis and Insights :

Global Curing Agents Market

Curing agents market will reach an estimated valuation of USD 8.26 billion by 2028, while registering this growth at a rate of 7.0% for the forecast period of 2021 to 2028. Curing agents market report analyses the growth, which is currently being growing due to the rising usages of the agent in the food preservation and flavouring process to draw moisture out of the food by the process of osmosis.

A curing agent is utilised to harden a surface or substance. They are added to the polymer surfaces so that the stronger the bond, the harder the surface of the material can ease the bonding of the molecular components. The primary feature is an improvement in hardness or viscosity. They consist mainly of three groups of compound-containing active-hydrogen, anionic and cationic initiators, and reactive cross- linkers.

Increasing growth of the construction as well as wind industry across the globe, surging levels of investment for the development of infrastructure in emerging economies, increasing demand due to its expanding applicability and eco-friendly nature, increasing need for high-performance, durable, and user-friendly goods, rising use of epoxy healing agents in applications such as coatings, wind energy, electrical and electronics, construction, composites, adhesives, and others are some of the major as well as vital factors which will likely to augment the growth of the curing agents market in the projected timeframe of 2021-2028. On the other hand, rising number of applications from developing economies along with the presence of a stellar electronics and electrical industry which will further contribute by generating massive opportunities that will lead to the growth of the curing agents market in the above mentioned projected timeframe.

Increasing number of environmental and health regulatory concerns along with increasing competition from the Chinese chemical manufacturers which will likely to act as market restraints factor for the growth of the curing agents in the above mentioned projected timeframe. Government has increased its regulations on the products which will become the biggest and foremost challenge for the growth of the market.

